The paper discusses Natural Language Inference (NLI) in the context of Natural Language Processing (NLP) applications, which falls under the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of structured knowledge, which is a central topic in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper presents a combination of techniques that harness knowledge graphs, which is a topic in both Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of external knowledge bases, which is a topic in Databases (cs.DB). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, and cs.DB.
